<item>
            <title>[LU-11500] kernel update [RHEL6.10 2.6.32-754.6.3.el6]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11500</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Upstream details at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2018:2846&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2018:2846&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A flaw named FragmentSmack was found in the way the Linux kernel handled reassembly of fragmented IPv4 and IPv6 packets. A remote attacker could use this flaw to trigger time and calculation expensive fragment reassembly algorithm by sending specially crafted packets which could lead to a CPU saturation and hence a denial of service on the system. (CVE-2018-5391)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;kernel: Integer overflow in Linux&apos;s create_elf_tables function (CVE-2018-14634)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
